response: {"Q0":"For Omgne sorting- always start with the image furthest to the left (image 1). Select it, and swap it with the image 2 on the right next to it. If they switch, continue to swap image 1 with the next image 3. If image 1 swaps with image 3, then check and see if image 2 swaps with image 3 to double check if it's lighter). After the first swap (image 1 w/image 2), always check if the image behind 1 will also swap. If it doesn't, continue to move Image 1 until it no longer moves. If (in this example) Image 1 does not swap with Image 4, it is heavier. If image 4 moves with image 5, make sure to check if Image 1 is heavier than image 5 has well and so on in descending order until no moves occur. Reminder- always start on the left. "}

["Start left from right and if there is a change keep passing it to the left until it can not move anymore then move on to the next block ","Start by comparing the first two blocks. Then progress by comparing the blocks in the 2nd and 3rd position, and then the 3rd and 4th, and so on.

Whenever a swap happens, keep note of the \"leading\" block that was placed ahead (to the right). If a swap does not happen, the block on the right that was compared becomes the new \"leading\" block. The block that was just swapped behind the \"leading\" block then needs to be compared to the block behind it. If a swap happens, again compare it to the block behind it. Repeat this until a swap does not happen or until it is placed in the first position. Then return to your \"leading\" block and compare it to the block ahead of it."]
